  <entry>
    <title>每周随记 第16期</title>
    <link href="http://pptx.online/blog/2019/01/03/16/"/>
    <id>http://pptx.online/blog/2019/01/03/16/</id>
    <published>2019-01-03T03:38:56.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-01-10T08:25:42.616Z</updated>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;地中海贫血的英文是Thalassemia，可其中没有Mediterranean，感觉有点怪，就查了下词源，发现thalass-是指海，在荷马史诗中特指地中海。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;before vowels thalass-, word-forming element meaning “sea, the sea,” from comb. form of Greek thalassa “the sea” (in Homer, when used of a particular sea, “the Mediterranean,” as opposed to okeanos), a word from a lost pre-Greek Mediterranean language. In Attic Greek thalatta, hence sometimes thalatto-.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
